<br>
I'd like to add that post 50 I'm starting to wish I had put more stats into agi, dex and sta during character creation. This is of course from the perspective of an ogre(maybe a troll too, Ruut?).<br>
<br>
One more thing to add about our ability to agro. It is all for not if you do not have the AC/HP gear to ensure that you don't die instantly, else you might as well be a ranger :P<br>
<br>
I think it was already said, but...<br>
<br>
Being an SK at the lower levels is ROUGH. You don't get FD and invis til lvl 30. Until then you are guard fodder. None of that sissy running to guards to save you from a_orc_02.<br>
<br>
You'll quickly learn to pay more attention to your enviroment if you wanna succeed<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
FD can seem very useless at times. If you wanna FD pull like a monk be warned. You have a long recast time on the FD spell. If you fail, chances are you are going to die if you don't have the AC/HP gear to live through to the next recast time.<br>
<br>
Best things about our class on a RAID: We can taunt any NPC off a caster reguardless of the NPCs level. This makes it alot easier for us to take control of a rampaging NPC that is storming through the camp picking off caster who decided it was a good idea to sit down and med while pulls are incoming. Secondly we are backup corpse summoners.<br>
<br>
Best thing about our class on an EPIC ENCOUNTER: We bring quick agro and can ensure that if anyone, we die first(much the same as some rangers do in an epic encounter). This gives other time to debuff the target, and gives the warriors time to match our agro(warriors build agro slowly/shadowknights build agro quickly).<br>
<br>
Best things about our class in a GROUP: We are excellent taunters, good tanks, good damage and debuff members. With good equipment we are good pullers, even better with the right equipment or levels(ie blood ember greaves or lvl 60 spell Death Peace).<br>
<br>
...but don't take my word for it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
